### 3. Parameter consistency enforcement (EKF2.cpp ~767-816)
- When `HGT_REF==BARO` and `BARO_CTRL==0`, EKF2 auto-forces `BARO_CTRL=1` (+ mavlink/event warning).
- When `HGT_REF==GNSS` and `VPOS` not set, EKF2 auto-ORs `VPOS|HPOS|VEL` into `GPS_CTRL`.
- **Important asymmetry to document:** with `HGT_REF==BARO`, GPS `VPOS` is NOT auto-enabled — so
  `EKF2_GPS_CTRL=1` genuinely leaves GPS altitude off.

